                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d318">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2798: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-26T18:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 26, 1918—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 26—5:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6023. Following joint telegram received from Allied Ministers dated Jassy,
                    November 20th: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Urgent. The delegates of the National Council of Transylvania have
                            arrived at Jassy in order to notify us as well as the Roumanian
                            Government, of their decision to proclaim their union with Roumania as
                            soon as the units of Transylvania now in process of formation shall have
                            established sufficient protection against the Hungarian troops.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
